snippet.title: New horned dinosaur named for the state of Utah
snippet.description: Meet Utahceratops and Kosmoceratops, two of Utah's older residents, now newly unearthed from Grand Staircase-Escalante National Monument in the southern portion of the state. snippet.title: Meet "dawn runner," a new dinosaur discovered in South America
snippet.description: Researchers from Argentina and the U.S. have announced the discovery of a new dinosaur named "Eodromaeus," meaning the dawn runner. snippet.title: New dinosaur that predates T. rex found in Utah
snippet.description: SALT LAKE CITY (AP) Paleontologists on Wednesday unveiled a new dinosaur discovered four years ago in southern Utah that proves giant tyrant dinosaurs like the Tyrannosaurus rex were around 10 million years earlier than previously believed.
